description:
Registrar Corp ayuda a empresas con el cumplimiento de los requisitos de la FDA.
Para asistencia inmediata: http://www.registrarcorp.com/livehelp
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------


Cuando las personas piensan en los requisitos regulatorios de etiquetado de FDA
la mayoría piensa en una tabla nutricional.
A pesar de que las tablas nutricionales son una parte importante de los requerimientos de FDA sobre el etiquetado de alimentos,
FDA regula muchos otros aspectos.
El alcance es bastante amplio.
Incluso el nombre de un producto puede ser regulado por FDA.
¿Sabía usted que para poder llamar a un producto "margarina",
el mismo debe cumplir con un grupo complicado de regulaciones
que especifican qué ingredientes puede contener?
FDA también regula cómo se deben declarar los ingredientes.
Los ingredientes deben ser declarados por sus nombres comunes
e incluir cualquier sub-ingrediente encontrado en los mismos.
FDA especifica el orden en el que deben presentarse así como el tamaño de letra utilizada en la impresión.
Los ingredientes alimenticios por sí mismos pueden ser regulados en una gran variedad de maneras.
Algunos son generalmente reconocidos como seguros, mientras que otros pueden tener requisitos estrictos respecto a su uso.
Los colorantes se encuentran dentro del grupo más estrictamente regulado y deben ser aprobados por FDA.
Piénselo dos veces antes de agregar esa tinta de calamar a su pasta mediterránea.
La tinta de calamar no está aprobada como un colorante y puede causar que su producto sea detenido.
La tabla nutricional puede verse simple, pero una enredada tela de regulaciones la gobiernan.
El tamaño de su empaque y la cantidad de nutrientes en su producto determinan qué tipo de tabla nutricional puede utilizar.
Incluso los tamaños de las líneas y si un nutriente es declarado en negrilla está descrito en la regulación.
Una gran parte de las actividades regulatorias de FDA está relacionada con las declaraciones en los productos.
Cualquier declaración relacionada a la cantidad o beneficio de los nutrientes en el producto debe cumplir las regulaciones.
Cualquier declaración relacionada al efecto del producto en la estructura o función del cuerpo también debe cumplir las regulaciones.
Las compañías usualmente desean hacer declaraciones como
 "reduce el colesterol" o "bajo en sodio", "libre de grasa", "apoya el sistema inmunológico", "baja la presión sanguínea".
FDA considera ciertas declaraciones apropiadas para suplementos alimenticios pero no para alimentos convencionales.
Las compañías deben entender los requisitos antes de realizar cualquier declaración en los productos.
Además, las compañías algunas veces hacen declaraciones agresivas de salud en sitios de internet o materiales promocionales.
FDA considera estas declaraciones parte del etiquetado de su producto como si estuviese directamente impreso en el mismo.
Productos han sido detenidos por declaraciones en sitios de internet incluso cuando esas declaraciones no se encontraban en el empaque primario.

Como puede darse cuenta, los requerimientos de etiquetado de FDA pueden ser complicados.
A pesar de que FDA divulga todos los requisitos de etiquetado por escrito,
debido a la diversidad de productos regulados por FDA,
no existe un sitio único donde encontrar todas las regulaciones de etiquetado.
Las regulaciones de etiquetado se encuentran en las miles de páginas del Código de Regulaciones Federales,
en incontables documentos guía,
revisiones SCOGS,
notificaciones GRAS,
cartas de aviso redactadas para compañías en violación
y enterradas en las notas de cientos de páginas en el Registro Federal.
Si usted desea más información sobre los requerimientos de etiquetado para su producto específico
o simplemente desea que alguien revise su etiqueta para asegurarse que está en cumplimiento con las regulaciones,
por favor contacte a Registrar Corp.
Llame a nuestras oficinas en Estados Unidos al teléfono 757-224-0177
o visite nuestra página de internet en http://www.registrarcorp.com
title: U.S. FDA Regulaciones de Etiquetado para Alimentos y Bebidas (Español)

description:
Multiple police agencies were called to Ferguson early Saturday morning following reports of violence.

About 200 protesters clashed with police at the height of the disturbance at the Ferguson Market, where they began looting.  Police said they tried to set the store on fire.

St. Louis County Police tell News 4 there has been more looting of stores near West Florissant.  According to police, a liquor store, an electronics store, and a beauty supply store were looted,

About 100 police officers in riot gear moved in to disperse the crowd.  One officer was injured by a thrown brick or rock.

Police said there was also at least one shooting victim rushed to Christian Northeast Hospital.  No other details about that shooting have been released, other than it took place at the intersection of West Florissant and Canfield Drive.

At one point, protesters locked their arms and turned their backs to police.

There are reports that peaceful protesters, including Alderman Antonio French, attempted to calm tensions.  Groups were seen blocking entrances to local stores to keep looters from entering.
There are no official reports of arrests being made.  As looting occurred, police dressed in riot gear mainly stood and watched, apparently under orders not to engage.

News 4's Russell Kinsaul reported police arrived on scene around 6:15 a.m. to make sure only authorized people were inside businesses as well as clearing parking lots. 

Community members also arrived to start the clean-up process for businesses damaged by looters.
title: Looters Rob Liquor Store In Ferguson, Missouri (8/16/2014) Michael Brown Shooting Aftermath

With this new configuration I am using less than 2 volts per cup. The connectors and container barely get warm anymore and the output is very close to what it was before.

description:
There are precise observations which indicate the reluctance of excess carbon within bainite or martensite to partition into adjacent austenite in spite of prolonged heat treatment at temperatures where carbon is mobile. To explain this, we report the first calculations of the solubility of carbon in tetragonal ferrite that is in equilibrium with austenite. It is found that the solubility is dramatically increased relative to the cubic form of ferrite, and the implications of this are discussed briefly.
http://www.msm.cam.ac.uk/phase-trans/2012/solubility.html
H. K. D. H. Bhadeshia, University of Cambridge
title: Equilibrium between tetragonal ferrite and austenite

description: Huge Coho run on Sept 17, 2011 in Douglaston Salmon Run Pulaski NY.  This video was shot at about 10:30am.  These fish had been coming up like this for an hour and continued until we left at 3:30pm. The glare makes it hard to see how many fish were moving though but my guess is that over 5000 came by us in 5 hours.   Wave after wave of 100 fish came every few minutes.  At some points there were 1000 fish swirling in circles going up and down for an hour before they continued up river.
title: Salmon River NY Coho Run Sept 17, 2011

description:
For submission to Enculturations Call for Cut-ups. William Burroughs  http://www.enculturation.net/Burroughs-CFC

I can remember in the early days of the Vietnamese war, they had these CIA men in remote outposts, which was then a center of terrorist activity. These people were bomb throwing terrorists and double agents. So they're there on—they don't pay, see. These are the Czar's, the Czarist Secret Police, just exactly reminiscent of the KGB. They even attacked a horned owl with their umbrellas, like so many animated cartoon figures—but one hell of a lot worse. 

They believed the earth was flat, and no wonder because that means trouble. They believed a man splitting his own head with an ax does not conform to your preconceived standards. He was one of us, whoever we are. His work will be judged on its own merit. 

They were both rather like the odor eaters in Tibetan mythology, smelling of raw onions and spirits, and they both had the same trick of half finished sentences... Both reminded me of scabs on sores. Both reminded me of the soft rich mud around the pool where cattle go to drink. Both are romantic heroes. 

They believed—incidentally, I think, under western eyes—such destinies no longer exist. 

They both require the midwifely services of a narrative—of a narrator.

But it is so strikingly similar to the American dream... 

It's very funny, actually. 

Sources: 
https://www.youtube.com/watch?feature=player_embedded&v=3dymsKE_N3A
https://www.youtube.com/watch?feature=player_embedded&v=4d3fDtxCiAQ

description: Logan Seymour, 10, who has defied odds by being picked for the English Kickboxing team after being told by doctors he would never be able to take part in competitive sport.   A schoolboy who was born without a HEEL has defied doctors by becoming a champion KICKBOXER.  Brave Logan Seymour has suffered from club foot since he was a baby but incredibly has no problem kicking his way to gold medals.  The 10-year-old was born with his left foot turned in and upwards and had to have his leg in a splint and plaster from the age of just six-weeks-old.  That was removed after six months but Logan was then given special shoes to wear and had daily physio from his mum to help push his foot back into place and form a heel.  Doctors warned his devastated parents it was unlikely their son would ever play sport because of the condition - which is also known as talipes.  But incredibly the youngster has now been picked to be part of the England kickboxing squad which will compete in the world championships in Portugal in November.
title: Schoolboy born without a heel becomes a kickboxing sensation.
